net.enilink.komma.model

Interface IModelSet

  • All Superinterfaces:
    INotifier<INotification>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IModelSet.Internal
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MemoryModelSetSupport, ModelSetSupport, PersistentModelSetSupport, RemoteModelSetSupport, SPARQLModelSetSupport

    public interface IModelSet
extends INotifier<INotification>
    An interrelated set of named graphs represented by IModel instances.

    A model set manages multiple ontologies and resolves owl:imports dependencies between them.

    Each model has its own IEntityManager that has read-write access to its named graph and read-only access to the named graphs of its owl:imports closure.

      • createModel

        IModel createModel(URI uri)
        Creates a new model, of the appropriate type, and returns it.

        It delegates to the model factory model to determine the correct factory, and then it uses that factory to create the resource and adds it to the contents. If there is no registered factory, null will be returned; when running within Eclipse, a default RDF/XML factory will be registered, and this will never return null.

        Parameters:
        uri - the URI of the model to create.
        Returns:
        a new model, or null if no factory is registered.

      • createModel

        IModel createModel(URI uri,
                   String contentType)
        Creates a new resource, of the appropriate type, and returns it.

        It delegates to the resource factory registry to determine the correct factory, and then it uses that factory to create the ontology and adds it to the contents. If there is no registered factory, null will be returned; when running within Eclipse, a default RDF/XML factory will be registered, and this will never return null.

        Parameters:
        uri - the URI of the resource to create.
        contentType - the content type identifier of the URI, or null if no content type should be used during lookup.
        Returns:
        a new ontology, or null if no factory is registered.

      • getModel

        IModel getModel(URI uri,
                boolean loadOnDemand)
        Returns the model resolved by the URI.

        A model set is expected to implement the following strategy in order to resolve the given URI to a model. First it uses it's URI converter to normalize the URI and then to compare it with the normalized URI of each resource; if it finds a match, that resource becomes the result. Failing that, it delegates to allow the URI to be resolved elsewhere. The important point is that an arbitrary implementation may resolve the URI to any model, not necessarily to one contained by this particular model set. If the delegation step fails to provide a result, and if loadOnDemand is true, a model is created and that model becomes the result. If loadOnDemand is true and the result model is not loaded, it will be loaded before it is returned.

        Parameters:
        uri - the URI to resolve.
        loadOnDemand - whether to create and load the model, if it doesn't already exists.
        Returns:
        the model resolved by the URI, or null if there isn't one and it's not being demand loaded.
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if a model can't be demand created.
        WrappedException - if a problem occurs during demand load.

      • getModelFactoryRegistry

        IModel.Factory.Registry getModelFactoryRegistry()
        Returns the registry used for creating a model of the appropriate type.

        An implementation will typically provide a registry that delegates to the global model factory registry. As a result, registrations made in this registry are local to this model set, i.e., they augment or override those of the global registry.

        Returns:
        the registry used for creating a model of the appropriate type.
